## CSS/Styling Rules

**CRITICAL**: When creating or modifying ANY CSS/styling:

1. **Location**: ALL CSS files MUST be placed in `app/assets/stylesheets/` directory
2. **Format**: ALWAYS use `.sass` format (indented syntax), NEVER use `.scss` or `.css`
3. **No exceptions**: Do not create CSS files in any other location (not in `app/javascript/`, not in `public/`, not anywhere else)

## Examples:
- ✅ `app/assets/stylesheets/components/_new_feature.sass`
- ✅ `app/assets/stylesheets/_new_styles.sass`
- ❌ `app/javascript/styles/component.css`
- ❌ `public/stylesheets/style.css`
- ❌ `app/assets/stylesheets/style.scss`

## When creating new features:
- If the feature needs styling, create a new `.sass` file in `app/assets/stylesheets/new/` and reference it in `app/assets/stylesheets/application.scss`
- Follow Rails asset pipeline conventions
- Use Sass indented syntax (no braces or semicolons)